  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0da7 \u0dad\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dba \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dba \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dd3\u0db4 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2\u0dab\u0dba\u0d9a \u0dba\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "China is closely monitoring the situation in this country",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesperson Wang Wengbin says that China is closely monitoring the development of the situation in Sri Lanka.",
        "He stated that China, as a friendly neighbor of Sri Lanka, sincerely hopes that all sectors of Sri Lanka will work for the basic needs of the country and its people and work together to quickly achieve social stability, economic recovery and livelihood improvements.",
        "Wang said this while commenting on the current situation in Sri Lanka at the regular press conference.",
        "After months of frustration with an unprecedented economic crisis, protesters stormed the Sri Lankan presidential palace in the capital Colombo on Saturday, Chinese media said, adding that the president announced his resignation on July 13, hours after leaving his home."
      ],
